y and mediality of the letter as well as its rhetorical communicative function, the value of correspondence as a form of historical documentation, and the history of letter archiving and publishing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aAuthors, GermanvCorrespondence. 0aGerman lettersxHistory and criticism. 0aGerman letters. 4aBrief. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aLetter.1 aBlamberger, Günter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBunzel, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDietzsch, Ina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEbert, Jens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErdbeer, Robert Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGolz, Jochen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGremmels, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrunenberg, Antonia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHelbich, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacob, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoachimsthaler, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoost, Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKramer, Olaf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKraus, Hans-Christof, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMayer, Mathias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMennecke, Ute, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNatterer, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular